      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">A 65-year-old man with a history of diabetes presents to a clinic in India, reporting a brown discoloration on the skin of his back and arm. He denies tobacco and alcohol use, has no history of blood transfusions, and does not take iron supplements or cook with iron utensils. After extensive testing, including a liver biopsy, he is diagnosed with primary hemochromatosis. Considering this patient&#39;s presentation and diagnosis, which set of conditions is referred to as &quot;bronze diabetes&quot;?</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2023/06/02/38.jpg\" style=\"height:202px; width:217px\" /></span></span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q4216111",
